'''Leo Statham XIX''' (5721-after 5778) was an Irish politician.

== Early life (5721-5739) ==
Statham was born in Dublin, Ireland. He is the only child of [[Leo Statham XVIII]] and his ex-girlfriend Freya Jenkins-Walsh.

== Career (5739-5759) ==
In 5739, Statham graduated from secondary school. He ran for election to the Dublin City Council and beat Oisin Bulkley.

In 5744, Statham ran for reelection and beat Mustafa Seikaly.

In 5749, Statham ran for a third term and beat Rachel Samuel.

In 5754, Statham ran for a fourth term and beat Niamh Williams.

In 5759, Statham did not run for a fifth term.

== Later life ==
Statham was alive in 5778, but his death date is unknown.

== Relationship and child ==
From 5739 to 5740, Statham dated a student named Aisling Taffe-O’Connor (5721-after 5778). They had a son, [[Leo Statham XX]].
